records.addlTxt: Received and Filed: Pretrial Services Supervision Report 11-07-2022

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell appeared by video.  Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke appeared by video for De'aiso Assunta Bell.  Attorney Amanda Kirklewski in court for State of Wisconsin on behalf of Attorney James C Griffin.

Case in court for a status conference.  Defense requests a projected guilty plea date.  Court scheduled the matter as requested.  Defendant is advised to appear in person at the next court date.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Plea hearing scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed: Pretrial Services Supervision Report 09-20-2022

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court cancel stayed bench warrant. Defense requests a status conference date. Court reinstated Justice Point Level 3 supervision. All other conditions remain the same. Case adjourned, Branch 2 via Zoom.  Status conference scheduled for September 20, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke in court.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Case scheduled for scheduling conference.  Defendant not appearing.  Defense counsel requests that the Court impose and stay a warrant.  State has no objection. Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until next court date.  Calendar call scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court, appear in person with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke, appear in person.  Abby Rockendorf appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 02, Judge Childs. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 02.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court, appear in person.  John Daniel Flynn appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. SPD has not appointed counsel. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in court with attorney Robert W Peterson.  Defendant De'aiso Assunta Bell in custody.  Patricia Irene Daugherty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  De'aiso Assunta Bell appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count 4.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
